Today a reader tomorrow a leader! Happy International Literacy Day! ` International Literacy Day is the annual reminder of the importance of literacy as a matter of dignity and human rights. Despite the efforts of the international community there are still 773 million adults and young people who lack basic literacy skills. The recent pandemic crisis negatively affected the learning of children young people and adults worldwide reminding of the existing gap between reality and desired outcomes. During the initial phase of the pandemic schools were closed disrupting the education of over 50% of the worldâ€™s student population. Our social entrepreneurs are always ready to fight back! In response to this wide-spread issue of illiteracy Sheila Osei Boakye from Ghana founded Literacy4Life an organization working to equip children with the fundamental skills required for reading and writing. It offers a faster and effective comprehensive language and literacy program for reading problems through Read Magic digital applications online courses interactive toolkits and reading camps. Since entering our Incubator program several years ago Sheila supported more than 34 000 children and youth.
